@asurve It seems that no changes to the `realease-build.sh` script are required. You can simply specify the branch when invoking the script with `--gitCommitHash="branch-name"`

I just did a `--dryRun` to verify it on my local clone

One could possibly change the name of the script parameter from `--gitCommitHash` to `--gitBranchOrCommitHash` or simply `--gitRef` and change the scripts usage text to make it clear

@asurve  when invoking the script with `--gitCommitHash="branch-name"` paramter you need to use an existing remote branch, the release-build script is not creating a new local branch

I just ran the unchanged script with  `--gitCommitHash="branch-name"` on Apache Bahir and accidentally missed to use the `--dryRun` flag. The release script finished without any error and created the release tag.

I would advocate to not introduce additional redundant if-then-else code blocks with potential for more errors.

This can be used for labelling where a matrix came from (for instance, "description": "I was generated by SystemML's Univariate Statistics"

Example writes:
```
A = matrix("1 2 3 4", rows=2, cols=2);
write(A, "results/A.csv", format="csv");
write(A, "results/Adesc.csv", format="csv", description="description 1");
write(A, "results/B.text", format="text");
write(A, "results/Bdesc.text", format="text", description="description 2");
write(A, "results/C.mm", format="mm");
write(A, "results/Cdesc.mm", format="mm", description="description 3");
write(A, "results/D.bin", format="binary");
write(A, "results/Ddesc.bin", format="binary", description="description 4");

X = 5;
Xdesc = "description " + X;
write(A, "results/Xdesc.csv", format="csv", description=Xdesc);

#This erroneously sets the description to "Ydesc"
Ydesc = "description 6";
if (1 == 1) {
    Ydesc = "this should be the description"
}
write(A, "results/Ydesc.csv", format="csv", description=Ydesc);
```

