Since our main algorithms are packaged in the jar, something like dmlFromResource does offer a simple way of accessing the script without needing to do something such as unpack the jar file or copy/paste the script from the file system or a URL. It's a great way to easily reference and run an algorithm and in no way prevents algorithm customization. If I would like to quickly demonstrate running an algorithm from the spark shell, most likely I would use dmlFromUrl (reference a script on github) or dmlFromReference (reference a script in the jar), and dmlFromResource would use the specific script packaged with the specific jar, so it's probably the better technique to use. So I would be in favor of adding dmlFromResource to the Python API.

If this PR looks good or if the Python needs any updates, please let me know.

